observations.recommendation:
We recommend that the LCE instruct the:
(a) MDRRMO to make regular inspection of, regularly maintain, and provide adequate safeguard on DRRM facilities and equipment to prevent their undue deterioration and/or misuse;
(b) Officials concerned to (i) observe the provision of paragraph 6.5 of NDRRMC-DBM-DILG Joint Memorandum Circular on the use of prior years’ unexpended LDRRMF; and (ii) make appropriate study on the responsiveness of a proposed flood control projects.

3.17	We recommended that the:
(a) Disaster Risk Reduction Management (DRRM) Officer regularly monitor and evaluate the utilization of Local Disaster Risk Reduction Management Fund (LDRRMF) based on the PPAs listed in the Local Disaster Risk Reduction Management Plan (LDRRMP);
(b) Budget Officer and Municipal Accountant to refrain from processing claims which are not related to disaster preparation, mitigation and preparedness;
(c) Municipal Social Welfare and Development Officer (MSWDO) gather complete turn-over documents for all relief goods received by the Municipality and Municipal Accountant recognize properly in the books the receipts thereof; and
(d) DRRM Officer and Municipal Accountant prepare and submit regularly the report on sources and utilization of DRRMF on or before the 15th day after the end of each month.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive and the MENRO:

 exert effort to expedite the establishment and completion of the  Category 1 Sanitary Landfill; 

involve closely the Barangay officials in the strict implementation on the existing environmental laws and intensify the information campaign on the “no segregation, no collection policy and the “no-littering policy” 

among the residents and tourists; 

seek the help of private companies/organizations in the conduct of a more aggressive and intensive information campaign on the proper segregation of waste and “no littering” policies; and 

exercise strong political will to implement the environmental laws on preserving and protecting the environment as mandated under Republic Act No. 9003.
